      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "- **Basic center:** one **tertiary aliphatic amine** (the piperidine nitrogen is substituted by **tert\u2011butyl**).  \n  - Expected to be **protonated at pH 7.4** (piperidine-like pKa typically ~10\u201311; N\u2011alkylation may lower slightly but still largely cationic).\n- **Ring system:** **piperidine** (saturated 6-membered ring).\n- **Hydrophobic/aromatic domains:** a **benzhydryl-like (diphenylmethyl/diaryl quaternary carbon)** motif: **two phenyl rings** attached to the same carbon on the piperidine ring (very hydrophobic, strong \u03c0 surface).\n- **Overall pharmacophore:** **cationic N + bulky hydrophobic/aromatic groups** in the same scaffold.\n- **Structural alerts:** strongly resembles known hERG-liable motifs:\n  - **piperidine + aromatic** (explicit alert you listed)\n  - **diphenyl/benzhydryl** motifs are common in hERG binders (large aromatic \u201cwings\u201d around a cation).",
