      "step_index": 11,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "- **Could steric bulk reduce binding?** The **tert\u2011butyl** could, in some cases, hinder optimal orientation of the cation or reduce access. But many potent blockers are also bulky; the channel cavity is large enough for substantial hydrophobes.\n- **Is the amine definitely protonated?** Even if N-alkylation lowers pKa somewhat, a tertiary piperidine-like amine is still expected to be **mostly protonated** at physiological pH \u2192 supports blockade.\n- **Any polar groups to reduce hERG?** None. Lack of polarity typically **increases** hERG risk (higher lipophilicity, stronger hydrophobic binding).",
